    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a lineup anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (70.94) and **Junior Caminero** (70.65), both of whom offer the highest efficiency floors against favorable matchups. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from an elite xwOBA of 0.393 and a matchup against Will Warren, while **Junior Caminero** finds himself in an ideal spot to capitalize on a +11% skill adjustment against the pitching profile of Bradley. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** (68.42) remains a prioritized start; despite a slight platoon penalty, his placement in the leadoff spot and his unparalleled ability to secure SBs make him a must-start in our pursuit of category scarcity. **Caleb Durbin** (67.42) rounds out our top-tier targets, benefiting from a massive +16% park adjustment and an advantageous look at Young, though we are monitoring the 34% rain risk in that stadium closely.\n\nOur optimization process was particularly nuanced at the periphery of the roster. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (50.22) served as the closest cut, narrowly missing the final lineup due to a daunting matchup against Emmet Sheehan\u2014whose 3.20 xERA represents the toughest arm on the board for our bench\u2014combined with a projected bottom-of-the-order assignment that sapped his efficiency score. We also saw solid potential from **Jerar Encarnacion** (48.33), but his matchup against Sandy Alcantara neutralized the benefit of the wind conditions. Conversely, **Dillon Dingler** (61.29) earns a spot in the starting rotation today, as his dynamic platoon advantage against Abbott (+14%) and the favorable SB environment created by the pitcher's delivery tempo outweigh the safer floor of some bench alternatives. We will continue to track the pending lineups for **Luke Raley**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Kyle Schwarber**, and **Josh Smith** to ensure our efficiency projections remain aligned with reality.",
